 ('6', '6', 'en_us', 'Pay a Parking Ticket', 'Pay your ticket online', '', 'https://prodpci.etimspayments.com/pbw/include/oakland/input.jsp', '<p>You have 21 days after the date the ticket was written to make a payment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"ways-to-pay\">Pay by Phone</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center</strong><br>Phone: (800) 500-6484<br>Please have your&nbsp;credit card on hand&nbsp;(Visa, Mastercard, Discover or American Express)</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Pay by&nbsp;Mail or&nbsp;In Person</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center</strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300 Oakland, CA 94612<br>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Additional In Person Locations</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parking ticket payment kiosks</strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza<br>Monday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eastmont Police Substation</strong><br>2651 73rd Avenue<br>Monday through Saturday from 8:00 a.m. to 4 p.m.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"by-mail\">Pay by Mail</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Mail your parking ticket&nbsp;and the full payment to:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parking Citation Assistance Center</strong><br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300<br>Oakland, CA 94612</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Refund Request Form</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>If you feel you are due a refund for overpayment for a parking ticket associated with your license plate, please complete and return a Refund Request Form.\r\nClick here to download the Refund Request Form.\r\nProvide proof of payment as detailed on the form.\r\nPlease allow four to six weeks for processing.\r\nCompleted forms and proof of payment can be submitted by mail, in person or by fax.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 id=\"mailin-person\">Mail/In Person</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Parking Citation Assistance Center<br>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 6300 Oakland, CA 94612<br>Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br>Wednesdays from 9:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.<br></p><p><br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Additional References</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li><a href=\"{entry:332:url}\">Costs of Common Parking Violations</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www2.oaklandnet.com/oakca1/groups/ceda/documents/marketingmaterial/oak044797.pdf\">Complete roster of parking violation fines from the OMC and California Vehicle Code</a></li><li><a href=\"http://library.municode.com/index.aspx?clientId=16308&stateId=5&stateName=California\">Oakland Municipal Code about parking violations</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.leginfo.ca.gov/cgi-bin/calawquery?codesection=veh\">California Vehicle Code</a></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[\"pinned\"]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-04 20:08:33', '2016-01-07 00:52:20', 'f20d6c8d-e817-4c50-a206-5cecfcf7d257'),
 ('7', '11', 'en_us', 'Free Parking on Plaid Friday & Saturdays until New Year\'s', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>As part of the Shop Oakland Grown for the Holidays campaign, the City of Oakland will offer&nbsp;free parking every Saturday until New Year\'s Day plus Plaid Friday (November 27).&nbsp;The free parking applies to on-street meters (both individual meters and multi-space kiosks), four City-owned parking lots and four City-owned parking garages. Posted time limits&nbsp;at meters&nbsp;still apply.</p>', '2015-12-09 00:00:00', 'As part of the Shop Oakland Grown for the Holidays campaign, the City of Oakland will offer free parking every Saturday until New Year\'s Day plus Plaid Friday (November 27). The free parking applies to on-street meters (both individual meters and multi-space kiosks), four City-owned parking lots and four City-owned parking garages. Posted time limits at meters still apply.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-10 19:26:54', '2015-12-10 22:58:01', '6f49b0d7-8101-4859-a00a-2b4996348e91'),
 ('8', '12', 'en_us', 'Oakland’s Minimum Wage Goes Up January 1, Deadline for noticing requirement is December 15', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Oakland’s Measure FF, a voter-enacted ballot measure passed in November 2014, provides annual increases to Oakland’s Minimum Wage based on the local Consumer Price Index (CPI). Effective January 1, 2016, the rate rises 30¢, from $12.25 to $12.55. The law requires that employers inform employees of the increase by December 15, 2015.</p>', '2015-12-09 00:00:00', 'Oakland’s Measure FF, a voter-enacted ballot measure passed in November 2014, provides annual increases to Oakland’s Minimum Wage based on the local Consumer Price Index (CPI). Effective January 1, 2016, the rate rises 30¢, from $12.25 to $12.55. The law requires that employers inform employees of the increase by December 15, 2015.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-10 19:37:05', '2015-12-10 22:58:16', '792b332f-3e05-43db-a84c-0dfebec5e544'),
 ('9', '13', 'en_us', 'Public Works', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Oakland Public Works plans, builds and maintains Oakland’s physical and environmental infrastructure for the residents, businesses and visitors of the city, making it a sustainable and desirable place to live, work, invest and visit.', '<p><strong>Brooke A. Levin</strong><br>Director of Oakland Public Works</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'She is an American Public Works Association Leadership Fellow with more than 30 years of public and private sector experience, including the past 22 years with the City of Oakland. She has been Assistant Director of Public Works for the past nine and half years, overseeing a $60 million dollar annual budget. In that role, she managed the operation and maintenance of parks, city facilities, street cleaning, garbage and recycling collection, environmental cleanup, tree services and sustainability. For ten years prior to that she was Oakland\'s first Environmental Services Manager. She also played a key role in planning and public works issues as a Policy Advisor to Mayor Elihu M. Harris from 1991 to 1994, and had a lead role in the aftermath of the Oakland Hills Firestorm. She is an artist, enjoys yoga and is the proud mother of two sons. Brooke has a Bachelor’s degree from the University of New Mexico.', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'opwcallcenter@oaklandnet.com', '<p>Main&nbsp;Phone: (510) 615-5566<br>TTY: (510) 238-3254<br>Oakland Recycles:&nbsp;(510) 238-SAVE<br>Volunteer Oppurtunites:&nbsp;(510) 238-7611</p>', '<p>250 Frank H. Ogawa Plaza, Suite 4314<br>Oakland, CA 94612</p>', '<p>Monday through Friday<br>8:00AM to&nbsp;5:00PM</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-10 19:52:47', '2016-01-21 00:02:47', '81984301-825c-4a48-9285-a94420af4a2f'),
 ('12', '16', 'en_us', 'Human Resources', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Our goal is to seek, engage, and promote a talented workforce that reflects the diversity and dynamic character of the City.', '<p><strong>Anil Comelo<br></strong>Human Resources Management Director</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Anil Comelo has more than 18 years of experience managing human resources functions. With a staff of 40 and an annual operating budget of $5.6M and a workers compensation budget of $22 million, he is responsible for directing the Recruitment and Classification, Benefits and Risk Management functions.', NULL, 'information', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Main Line: (510) 238-3112\r\nJob Hotline (24-hr access): (510) 238-3111\r\nPublic Safety Job Hotline: (510) 238-6465\r\nCertification Hotline: (510) 238-3528', 'Lionel J. Wilson Building \r\n150 Frank Ogawa Plaza\r\n2nd Floor\r\nOakland, CA 94612', 'Monday through Friday\r\n8:30am to 5:00pm', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-10 23:28:13', '2016-01-20 23:37:57', 'f9672cd7-4a0d-4d3e-a671-64d73674ebd4'),
