 ('1182', '662', '3', '512', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"512\",\"title\":\"Read El Nino Press Releases\",\"slug\":\"el-nino-press-releases\",\"postDate\":1453180740,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"482\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>Oakland Press Releases & Presentations<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>January 7, 2016:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/ElNino\\/OAK056596\\\"><strong>Oakland Offers El Nino Preparedness Workshops<\\/strong><\\/a><\\/li><li>January 5, 2016:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/ElNino\\/OAK056594\\\"><strong>Presentation to Oakland City Council&nbsp;on Public Works&nbsp;El Ni\\u00f1o Preparation<\\/strong><\\/a><\\/li><li>December 22, 2015:&nbsp;<strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/ElNino\\/OAK056422\\\">Three El Nino Safety \\\"How To\\\" Videos<\\/a>\\\"<\\/strong><\\/li><li>December 9, 2015:<strong>&nbsp;<\\/strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/pwa\\/documents\\/pressrelease\\/oak056236.pdf\\\"><strong>Urging Residents & Businesses to Prepare&nbsp;for Winter Storms<\\/strong><\\/a><\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"Learn more about City-wide El Nino Preparation\"}}', '2016-01-19 05:20:56', '2016-01-19 05:20:56', '486f9a91-4c85-460c-8141-647217987782'),
 ('1192', '672', '3', '512', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"512\",\"title\":\"Preparation Tips & Tricks for Winter Storms\",\"slug\":\"preparation-tips-tricks-for-winter-storms\",\"postDate\":1453181422,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"462\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Use this guide to prepare for severe weather situations<br>including heavy rains, flooding, high winds and power outages.<br>Follow these basic guidelines to prepare, respond and recover from<br>strong winter storms.<span><\\/span><\\/p><p><strong>For Your Family<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Be prepared for flooding, power outages and road closures<\\/li><li>Watch this FEMA video:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=LviZ4pZrqu8\\\">Family Communications Plan and Emergency Kit<\\/a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/li><li>Make contingency plans for shelter should your home flood or become inaccessible<\\/li><li>Discuss evacuation plans with your family now<\\/li><li>Know emergency procedures and evacuation plans at your children\'s schools<\\/li><li>Keep&nbsp;3-7 days of water, food, medicine and other supplies on hand for all family members and pets<\\/li><li>Click on&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ready.gov\\/\\\">www.Ready.gov<\\/a>&nbsp;for Family Plans, emergency kit lists, and so much more for you and yours!<\\/li><li>Keep your pets safe and warm also, by&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/Government\\/o\\/OFD\\/s\\/CORE\\/OAK026272\\\">preparing ahead of time with these tips<\\/a>.<\\/li><\\/ul><strong>For Your Home<\\/strong>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Get flood insurance, now! It can take 30 days for policies to take effect<\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ktvu.com\\/community\\/56230229-video\\\">Watch this video about flood insurance<\\/a>, by Bay Area People<\\/li><li>Watch this video:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/147505317\\\">How to Create Sandbags<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.floodsmart.gov\\/toolkits\\/flood\\/downloads\\/WestCoastRainySeason-OT2007.pdf\\\">FEMA\'s FloodSmart Tool Kit<\\/a><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.water.ca.gov\\/floodmgmt\\/docs\\/brochure_floodfightingathome.pdf\\\">How to Fight Flooding, by California Dept. of Water Resources<\\/a><\\/li><li>Know Your Flood Risk: Search your address&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.floodsmart.gov\\/floodsmart\\\">www.Floodsmart.gov<\\/a><\\/li><li>Check your roof, rain gutters and chimney for holes and clear debris<\\/li><li>Inspect and clean drains around your home and its foundation<\\/li><li>Make sure windows are watertight<\\/li><li>If you rent, discuss any issues with the property manager<\\/li><li>Place sandbags in flood-prone areas<\\/li><li>Ensure outdoor lights are working<\\/li><li>Check your fences, your gates and your driveway for sturdiness and&nbsp;clear debris<\\/li><li>Clear your yard of debris<\\/li><li>Secure patio furniture, garbage cans and other items that might move if flooded<\\/li><li>Review your insurance and consider flood insurance.&nbsp;United&nbsp;Policy Holders&nbsp;Insurance&nbsp;has a helpful website at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.uphelp.org\\/\\\">www.uphelp.org<\\/a>.&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www2.oaklandnet.com\\/oakca1\\/groups\\/pwa\\/documents\\/agenda\\/oak056634.pdf\\\" target=\\\"true\\\">Download a copy of our \\\"Storm Ready\\\" brochure.<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"Prepare in Advance. Keep your family, pets and property safe.\"}}', '2016-01-19 05:30:22', '2016-01-19 05:30:22', '8460e65c-454f-4d28-85f6-d475d11c692e'),
 ('1202', '682', '3', '512', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"512\",\"title\":\"Adopt a City Storm Drain\",\"slug\":\"adopt-a-city-storm-drain\",\"postDate\":1453181744,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"462\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The City \\\"Adopt a drain\\\" program<strong>&nbsp;<\\/strong>seeks volunteers to help keep storm drains clear of debris. By keeping storm drain inlets clear, you can help prevent flooding during storms.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Want to learn more?&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Watch this Bay Area People&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ktvu.com\\/community\\/56230465-video\\\">video about the Adopt a Drain Program<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Still have questions?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Call:&nbsp;(510) 238-7630<\\/p>\",\"5\":\"www.adoptadrainoakland.com\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"Adopt a Drain\",\"4\":\"Volunteer to Adopt a Storm Drain in Your Neighborhood\"}}', '2016-01-19 05:35:44', '2016-01-19 05:35:44', '5a011b1c-e98d-4040-9626-49f5eba0658a'),
 ('1212', '692', '3', '512', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"512\",\"title\":\"Pick Up Sandbags & Plastic Sheeting for Your Neighborhood\",\"slug\":\"pick-up-sandbags-plastic-sheeting-for-your-neighborhood\",\"postDate\":1453182045,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"462\",\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The City of Oakland will provide emergency sandbags and plastic sheeting when heavy rains are forecast. Each Oakland resident and business owner may pickup sandbags (up to 10)&nbsp;and plastic sheeting (up to 20 feet) at the following locations, as long as supplies last.&nbsp;Bring your ID to prove residency. Be prepared to fill your own if needed.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Municipal Service Center<\\/strong>, 7101 Edgewater Drive<br>Monday \\u2013 Friday, 8 a.m. \\u2013 4 p.m.<br>Saturday & Sunday, 8 a.m. \\u2013 4:30 p.m.<br>After Hours (at entry gate) 4:30 p.m. \\u2013 8 a.m.<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Drainage Services Facility<\\/strong>, 5921 Shepherd Canyon<br>Monday \\u2013 Friday, 8 a.m. \\u2013 4 p.m.<br>After Hours (at entry gate) 4:30 p.m. \\u2013 8 a.m.<\\/p><p><strong>Need more bags?&nbsp;<\\/strong>You can pick up bags at your local hardware, garden or home improvement stores.&nbsp;<\\/p><p><strong>Want to learn how to make a sandbag?<\\/strong> <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=MRylOmhwgX8\\\" target=\\\"true\\\">Watch this video.<\\/a><\\/p><p><strong>Want to learn how to use plastic sheeting?<\\/strong> <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=oKxRIr-qaV4\\\" target=\\\"true\\\">Watch this video.<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"5\":\"\",\"92\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"The City of Oakland Offers Sandbags & Plastic Sheeting to Residents and Businesses\"}}', '2016-01-19 05:40:46', '2016-01-19 05:40:46', '36b4ef98-4b58-47d2-a872-35eefed93c57'),
