 ('72', 'field', '1', 'en_us', ' an obstruction permit allows you to park the pod portable storage unit or moving truck in one site for a limited amount of time how the obstruction permit works the obstruction permit tells nearby property owners that they can not park in the permitted site for a limited amount of time you may only block the street or right of way that you are moving from or to you need to post the no parking sign s that you receive with the obstruction permit at least 72 hours 3 days before parking the portable storage unit or moving truck how to apply for an obstruction permit you can only apply for an obstruction permit in person at the permit center to avoid long line visit the permit center early in the day before the busiest time from 11 a m to 4 p m please bring the following information site address dates required number of parking spaces required one parking space is 25 feet long meter numbers if you are blocking parking meters contact phone number for the company or person applying if related to work requiring permit please reference permit application number traffic control plan only required if you need to block traffic refer to the traffic engineering website http www2 oaklandnet com government o pwa o ec o ts oak026469 visit the permit center once you arrive at the permit center s information counter ask for an obstruction permit when your number is called proceed to the indicated counter provide the required information pay the permit fee the permit center accepts cash checks payable to the city of oakland and most major credit cards where to apply for an obstruction permit locationhours permit center 250 frank h ogawa plaza 2nd floor oakland ca 94612 mondays tuesdays thursdays and fridays from 8 a m to 4 p m wednesdays from 9 30 a m to 4 p m last wednesday of each month from 10 a m to 4 p m cost of the obstruction permit the cost of an obstruction permit varies the cost depends on the period of time for the permit the number of parkin