 ('182', 'field', '1', 'en_us', ' if you contested a parking ticket and you are not satisfied with the decision you can request an administrative hearing what you need to know once you receive the decision from contesting your ticket you have 21 days to schedule a hearing you can request a hearing either in person or or by mail you must pay a deposit equal to the amount of the fine before scheduling a hearing request a hearing make your request in person or by mail to parking citation assistance center hearing dept 250 frank h ogawa plaza suite 6300 oakland ca 94612 pay the deposit if you cannot afford the deposit you can request a hearing deposit fee waiver by phone or by mail by mail click here to download the hearing deposit waiver form http www2 oaklandnet com oakca1 groups ceda documents marketingmaterial oak044809 pdf mail to the administrative hearing dept 250 frank h ogawa plaza suite 6300 oakland ca 94612 by phone call the parking citation assistance center at 800 500 6484 what happens next you will receive a notice by mail with the date and time of the hearing all hearings are held monday through friday between 9 a m and 4 p m the hearing will be held at eastmont mall police substation 2651 73rd avenue upper level oakland ca if you cannot attend your scheduled hearing you have two options rescheduling a hearing you have two options if you cannot attend the scheduled hearing reschedule the hearing call the hearing department at 510 238 4484 at least five calendar days before the scheduled hearing request a hearing by mail send a letter detailing your dispute and include all the required documentation '),
